   NEWYEAR-SITTERS (Undated) _ On New Year's Eve, many of the
1,000-some couples attending the Memphis Junior League's charity
ball will bring their children along. So the parents can be free to
cavort, they have coralled 40 baby sitters from the Annie's Nannies
agency. They will pay the sitters $330, triple the agency's usual
rate. So it will be in most big cities and their affluent suburbs
this New Year's Eve. Placement services say they are running short
of the nation's sitters _ baby sitters, pet sitters and building
sitters, or security guards _ who free others to celebrate. By
Peter T. Kilborn.
