<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-23 01:57 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A7342 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u s BC-FBN-SAINTS-DITKA-HNS &LR;      12-23 1291
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-SAINTS-DITKA-HNS </SLUG>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By JOHN McCLAIN  
 c. 1999, Houston Chronicle  
With two games remaining in the regular season, the New Orleans
Saints are embroiled in so much turmoil that coach Mike Ditka might
be out of a job after three seasons.
<TEXT>
<P>
   After the Saints received national attention for trading eight
draft choices, including first- and third-round picks in 2000, to
select Heisman Trophy winner Ricky Williams in the first round,
nothing has gone right.
</P>
<P>
   Williams has been in and out of the lineup because of ankle
injuries, and the Saints are in a 2-14 backslide, with a five-game
losing streak and only one victory since a season-opening win over
Carolina.
</P>
<P>
   ``With anything in life, there comes a point where you have to
address all problems, and we'll address all the problems,'' Ditka
said.
</P>
<P>
   And the problems continue to mount.
</P>
<P>
   If the Saints lose their last two games to Dallas and Carolina,
as expected, they will be 2-14. If Cleveland also finishes 2-14,
the Saints will earn the first pick in the draft because they
played an easier schedule than the Browns.
</P>
<P>
   But the Saints won't have the top pick. It belongs to Washington
because of the Williams trade.
</P>
<P>
   The Saints aren't losing close games, either. The defense, a
strength the last two seasons, has collapsed. The Saints have
surrendered at least 30 points in their last six defeats.
</P>
<P>
   An offense that was going to count so heavily on Williams, who
has missed the last four games because of an ankle injury, averages
only 15.4 points, 28th in the league. When the Saints host the
Cowboys on Friday, they will start their fourth quarterback this
season _ Jake Delhomme.
</P>
<P>
   Delhomme follows Billy Joe Hobert, Billy Joe Tolliver and Danny
Wuerffel, who have been injured or ineffective. Delhomme has been
buried so deep on the bench, he doesn't even classify as a
journeyman.
</P>
<P>
   At the center of the controversy is the volatile Ditka, who is
experiencing the worst season of his 14-year coaching career. There
are reports that owner Tom Benson wants to reach a settlement with
Ditka on his contract, which has three years left at a total value
of $6 million.
</P>
<P>
   Benson issued a vehement denial, but he hasn't given Ditka the
dreaded vote of confidence, which would almost guarantee his exit.
</P>
<P>
   ``They're full of ,'' Benson said about a Fox report last
weekend that he will buy out Ditka's contract. ``I don't know how
they came across a report like that. All they're doing is hurting
people with a statement like that.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've already said everything I'm going to say on the matter.
I'm not going to make any decisions until the season is over. This
is not the time nor the place to say anything else. At the end of
the season, I'll do whatever I think is necessary.''
</P>
<P>
   After exploding several times earlier in the season when his
behavior was perplexing to his players and fans, Ditka has been
rather subdued of late.
</P>
<P>
   ``I might not have a future (with the Saints),'' Ditka said.
``If we were to fall prey to the whims of a few of the people
(reporters) in this audience, I wouldn't have a future, would I? I
stand behind all the decisions I've made.''
</P>
<P>
   There already have been lists of possible replacements in the
New Orleans media.
</P>
<P>
   Ditka and general manager Bill Kuharich, who received a contract
extension before the season, are under fire. Benson isn't showing
his hand, but because attendance is down and the fans and media are
howling for changes, he is expected to do something after the
season.
</P>
<P>
   There is even speculation about which television job Ditka will
take next season.
</P>
<P>
   ``I came to grips with my life a long time ago,'' Ditka said.
``No matter what happens here, this is nothing like what happened
to me in Chicago. I happen to like Tom and have a great deal of
respect for him. Whatever happens here, I'm a big boy. I'm mature
enough to accept it and go on.''
</P>
<P>
   Naturally, losing and the widespread speculation about Ditka
have been distracting for the Saints. The 12 losses are the most of
his career. It is the third-most defeats the Saints have suffered.
</P>
<P>
   The Saints were swept by the AFC this season for the first time
since 1985. Longtime Saints fans are calling this season the worst
since they were 1-15 in 1980, leading former owner John Mecom to
hire Bum Phillips.
</P>
<P>
   If Williams had been healthy all season, the Saints probably
would have a better record. The idea was to hitch the wagon to him
and let him help them improve on back-to-back 6-10 records.
</P>
<P>
   Williams has rushed for 816 yards but has scored only two
touchdowns. To make matters worse, the Saints look terrible because
Indianapolis bypassed Williams for Edgerrin James, who leads the
AFC with 1,400 yards rushing and will be voted NFL Offensive Rookie
of the Year.
</P>
<P>
   Ditka is hoping Williams will be able to play against the
Cowboys, but he won't take unnecessary chances.
</P>
<P>
   ``It'd be foolish to jeopardize his career,'' Ditka said. ``When
he's ready to play, he'll play.''
</P>
<P>
   Ditka insists he has no regrets about making the Williams trade,
and he doesn't care what people around the NFL say about it.
</P>
<P>
   ``What's the matter with it?'' he said. ``My life has never been
predicated by what the league thinks. I've never tried to (make a
decision) because the league says this. The league, to me, is not
the higher authority. We made a decision we thought was best for
the Saints.
</P>
<P>
   ``The young man's an outstanding football player, and he's been
hurt. You retrospectively say you could have done better with seven
draft picks instead. Maybe, maybe not. That's questionable.
</P>
<P>
   ``I still think we've got the pieces in the puzzle upside down
right now. That's what's happened, but I think he's an awfully good
football player. You can do anything you want to do. I'm not going
to back off our decision. I didn't care about what people said
about us back in April, and I don't care what they say about it
now.''
</P>
<P>
   What the Saints have needed more than anything is a quarterback.
Ditka wants another veteran next season, but they need to draft a
young one they can develop, a quarterback who gives the fans hope.
</P>
<P>
   ``I wish that my confidence in the quarterback situation would
have been rewarded a little bit more, that the kid could have
stayed healthy,'' Ditka said of Hobert. ``He was the guy who I
thought was going to be our starting quarterback. Not that he
hasn't played well at times, but he hasn't been healthy enough.
That's a problem.''
</P>
<P>
   Although Ditka has tried to convince everyone that he has
mellowed over the last few years, they know it's not true. They
know he is in agony over losing.
</P>
<P>
   ``My disappointment's greater than a lot of people's,'' he said.
``We're going to try to correct it. I'm going to do my best as long
as I'm in this organization to get it right. That's all I'm going
to do.''
</P>
<P>
   Ditka insists he wants to return in 2000. Some wonder why he
doesn't just throw up his hands and say he is finished.
</P>
<P>
   ``You know what?'' Ditka said. ``We're 2000 years from the birth
of Christ. We're going to have Christmas on the 25th. I'm going
into the twilight of my life. I'm just enjoying it.
</P>
<P>
   ``Why would I worry about the scrutiny of others? Have you ever
read it's not the critic that counts? Unless you've been in the
arena, you don't know anyway. It's easy to point the finger, and
after the fact, Jack.
</P>
<P>
   ``After the fact, Jack, I have the answer, and I have the
solution, but when the game's on the line, do you really have the
answer or the solution? No, and that's why any decision we make on
the sidelines, the determining factor at the end of the season we
make is still based on how we execute on the field.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
