r l BC-STYLE-LAUDER24-COX     12-23 0422
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-STYLE-LAUDER24-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    `First Lady of Beauty' aims to capture sights through photos
 &HT;    By Staci Sturrock
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Evelyn Lauder is a woman of diverse
passions.
</P>
<P>
   Dubbed ``America's First Lady of Beauty,'' she's the senior
corporate vice president of the Estee Lauder companies, the
cosmetics empire founded by her mother-in-law.
</P>
<P>
   She's the founder and president of the Breast Cancer Research
Foundation, which has handed out more than $13.5 million in grants
since 1993.
</P>
<P>
   A nature lover, she's a photographer of landscapes and outdoor
still lifes who donates the proceeds from her work to breast cancer
research.
</P>
<P>
   Lauder, 63, visited Palm Beach recently for the opening of an
exhibition of her photographs at the Chase Manhattan Private Bank.
The show will remain up through Jan. 15.
</P>
<P>
   Dressed in a blue silk Oscar de la Renta suit, Lauder took time
out to offer her opinions...
</P>
<P>
   On photography: ``The creative process is so extraordinarily
exciting. I cannot stop. I need this for my soul.'' That's why she
packs her camera no matter where she and her husband, Leonard,
travel, whether it's to the base of a Venezuelan waterfall or to
the peaks of Colorado mountains.
</P>
<P>
   On her subject matter: ``It has a great deal to do with light
and how it plays off things,'' she says. ``It's just very
haphazard. If I see something beautiful, I grab it.'' Subjects in
her Chase Manhattan show include Indonesian fishing boats, Turkish
temples and 1950s Chevrolets in Cuba.
</P>
<P>
   On her choice of camera: The Olympus IS30. ``It's a spectacular
camera that can do a great many things, but it's automatic.''
</P>
<P>
   On sun protection: Always a hat or baseball cap (''I have a
great straw hat that ties under my chin''). A caftan or long shirt
over her swimsuit (''Even if I'm snorkeling, I'm wearing a
T-shirt''). And two layers of sunscreen (Estee Lauder's Resilience
Lift cream with an SPF of 15, followed by a more traditional
sunscreen).
</P>
<P>
   On her favorite spot outdoors in New York City: The clean, green
sweep of Central Park, where she walks regularly with her husband.
(She's a board member of the Central Park Conservancy and the Parks
Council.)
</P>
<P>
   On getting everything done: ``I am so disorganized. I have such
a mess on my desk.'' She hires good help _ one whose sole job is
riding herd on the 2,000 Christmas cards Lauder sends to friends,
family and business associates.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
