produces themed features budgets each day. Here is the schedule:
</P>
<P>
   Monday for Tuesday: Technology
</P>
<P>
   Tuesday for Wednesday: Automotive, personal finance and home &AMP;
garden
</P>
<P>
   Wednesday for Thursday: Food, CD reviews, video reviews
</P>
<P>
   TODAY: Movie reviews, travel, books and fashion
</P>
<P>
   Friday for Saturday: Religion and science &AMP; health
</P>
<P>
   In addition, separate budgets move daily with spot news, sports,
business and commentary.
</P>
<P>
   Stories are moving in the category they're listed under. Stories
moving to duplicate categories are marked. An ETA is given if a
story will move after 8 p.m. Eastern.
</P>
<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   SAVE TIME: Stories marked as a CoxNet layout are available for
purchase in paginated form: http://nytsyn.com/syndicate/pageex
</P>
<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   WALKER _ ATLANTA _ Emory University professor Vanessa Siddle
Walker is a rising star in academia. She recently was awarded the
prestigious Grawemeyer prize _ it comes with $200,000 _ for a book
she authored that details the success of a black school in the
segregated south. We take a look at her life and explore her
controversial views on education. (Blake, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   FASHION
</P>
<P>
   STYLE-LAUDER _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Evelyn Lauder is a woman
of diverse passions. Dubbed ``America's First Lady of Beauty,''
she's the senior corporate vice president of the Estee Lauder
companies, the cosmetics empire founded by her mother-in-law. She's
the founder and president of the Breast Cancer Research Foundation,
which has handed out more than $13.5 million in grants since 1993.
(Sturrock, Palm Beach Post). 20. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   CAROLEE _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Carolee Friedlander's journey
from struggling homemaker to super CEO is the stuff of which
entrepreneurial legends are made. Back in 1972, the young mother of
three started stringing necklaces at her kitchen table. From those
humble beginnings sprang an eponymous jewelry empire. (Sturrock,
Palm Beach Post). WITH PHOTOS. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL
</P>
<P>
   HOLY LAND PACKAGE
</P>
<P>
   JERUSALEM _ The Holy Land will be bursting with milennium
tourists and celebrants. But where better to be than following the
footsteps of Jesus. Special Israel section. Lots of art. Lede-in to
package. (Belkin, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WITH SIDEBARS
</P>
<P>
   GALILEE _ MOUNT OF BEATITUDES, Israel _ A tour bus stopped on
the slope of the Mount of the Beatitudes to let passengers watch a
shepherd herding his sheep. Except for his leather jacket and khaki
pants, he could have stepped from a scene 2,000 years ago. These
are the images that bring the Bible to life for many people and the
reason they make the long trip to Israel. More than the churches
and monuments, it is the gentle hills, the silver-blue beauty of
the Sea of Galilee and the rushing water of the River Jordan that
draw people to Galilee. (Blackerby, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MEGIDDO _ MEGIDDO, Israel _ When the final battle between good
and evil is fought, the book of Revelation tells us, it will be
fought here at a mountain at the entrance to the Jezreel Valley.
The mountain is called, in Hebrew, Har Megiddo, the Hill of
Megiddo. Bastardized by the Greeks, this battlefield became known
as Harmagedon. Today, Armageddon. (Belkin, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MAALULA _ MAALULA, Syria _ If you want to travel 2,000 years
back in time, to hear words like those spoken by Jesus and his
contemporaries in Jerusalem farther to the south, this stunning
oasis is the place to do it. (Salome, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
