<P>
   BUSINESS/FINANCIAL NEWS (``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CAREER-BOOKS (Undated) _ A handful of the career books that come
out each year are so wonderful that I write about them right away;
most of the rest get discarded in a hurry. But there is a third
group: Some books are intriguing enough to be useful to some
people, but have one flaw or another that keeps me from
wholeheartedly recommending them. Here are four such books. By DAVE
MURPHY.
</P>
<P>
   COKE-SHAKESPEARE (San Francisco) _ The Coca-Cola Co.'s recent
troubles might not have been so bad if executives there had paid
more attention to a classic. No, not Classic Coke, but classic
Shakespeare. Namely,
</P>
<P>
   ``Hamlet.'' ``They totally mishandled the crisis in Belgium on
the health scare,'' said Kenneth Adelman, coauthor of ``Shakespeare
in
</P>
<P>
   Charge: The Bard's Guide to Leading and Succeeding on the
Business Stage.'' He said Coca-Cola tried to downplay the tainted
Coke rather than being open with the public, and now Chairman and
Chief Executive Douglas Ivester is stepping down as the company
continues to sputter. By DAVE MURPHY.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT NEWS (``e'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FILM-SUNDAY (Los Angeles) _ Actors Cameron Diaz and Dennis Quaid
lead the cheers for their new movie, ``Any Given Sunday,'' a
football saga that tackles the good, bad and ugly of professional
football. The three-hour film is directed by Academy Award-winning
filmmaker Oliver Stone. By BRUCE WESTBROOK.
</P>
<P>
   FILM-REVIEW-MOTHER (Undated) _ Film director Pedro Almodovar has
dedicated ``All About My Mother'' to ``all actresses who have
played actresses, to men who act and become women, to all the
people who want to be mothers.'' It is a romantically labyrinthine
tribute that beautifully assesses the nature of facades. Once you
peel away the performance, what's left is the emotion it masks. By
WESLEY MORRIS.
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO-REVIEWS (Undated) _ Reviews of movies ``Summer of Sam,''
``American Pie'' and ``Run Lola Run,'' which are being released on
videotape. By BRUCE WESTBROOK.
</P>
<P>
   LIFESTYLE/FEATURES (``l'' category)
</P>
