<HEADLINE>
YOUR WISH IS IT`S COMMAND(OBOT)
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(Eds: EMBARGOED until Saturday, Dec. 25) 
By CAROL BIDWELL 
c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   For those who'd like to hear more of the pitter-patter of tiny
feet around the house at holiday time, the Space Battle 2000
Commandobot might be just the ticket. The 18-inch-tall plastic
critter won't get you a cup of coffee or make the bed, but it fires
toy missiles, makes really neat sound effects and, best of all,
responds to your voice commands.
</P>
<P>
   The robot comes with a headset transmitter for the operator to
wear, and can be programmed to respond _ with voice acknowledgment
and flashing lights _ to any ``master's'' voice giving up to 12
commands.
</P>
<P>
   The Commandobot, made by MGA Entertainment of North Hills,
retails for about $100 in toy, mass merchandise and department
stores. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-23-99 1357EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
