   DOW _ Stocks rise again, with the Dow up 200 points at once
time. Seasonal factors and the momentum among technology stocks
appear to be workding again. (Walker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   MEDIAMETRIX _ Media Metrix lists top Web sites of the holiday
season. Not necessarily the best, just the top ones. (Katz, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   Y2K-SECURITY _ The triple threat of the holidays, Y2K
uncertainty and the renewed acts of terrorism have helped boost
business for security firms this year. With the New Millenium a
week away, many of them are booked solid and some have had to turn
away business. Some security guards are getting $20 an hour to work
Y2k. The security scenario is one more tale of a city bulging with
jobs and no one to take fill them. (Joyner, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   SHOPLIFTING _ It's a gangbuster holiday season for retailers,
but it's also one for shoplifters. The more shoppers in retail
stores, the greater the chance that the employees will be
distracted. Thieves are lifting everything from athletic shoes to
CD's, which rank among the nation's most stolen items, according to
a 1998-1999 study conducted by Loss Prevention Specialists, a
consulting group in Winter Park, Fla. (Degross, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BELLSOUTH _ ATLANTA With the millennium rapidly approaching,
BellSouth is lending a helping hand to CARE, the international
humanitarian relief organization, to assist with its Year 2000
readiness program. (Kanell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   TECHNOLOGY
</P>
<P>
   WEB-CHURCHES _ AUSTIN, Texas _ You'd think that the Internet,
with its reputation for perpetuating pornography and its new bent
as a shopping mecca, would be enough to discouarage the Web as a
serious place to begin a spiritual journey. But houses of worship
are hoping that the Internet will educate, inspire and spread the
word as they rush to create online presences to promote their
churches, synagogues and even online-only religions. (Gallaga,
Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
