war in Chechnya is nearing an end. Grim details emerge of an
alleged massacre by Russian troops. Top US diplomat accuses Moscow
of treating civilians as ``terrorists.'' By David Filipov. 1000
words.
</P>
<P>
   UN-MISTAKE (New York) _ Debt-burdened single mother says she's
suing the United Nations for freezing her bank account. UN says it
took the action after it mistakenly deposited $700,000 in her
account because of an account ID number error. By Joe Lauria. 600
words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-PARDONS (Washington) _ President Clinton pardons Freddie
Meeks, one of the last survivors of the Port Chicago 50, a group of
black sailors whose conviction for mutiny during World War II
became a civil rights cause and helped spur integration of the
armed services. By John A. Farrell. (w and a coding)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; POLITICS (p) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CAMPAIGN-MCCAIN (Undated) _ Just two days after George W. Bush
said he would begin sharpening his differences with John McCain,
Americans for Tax Reform launches a TV campaign in New Hampshire
that charges McCain with hurting Republicans and the conservative
movement. By Jill Zuckman. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   COPKILLER-MANHUNT (Holyoke, Mass.) _ The intense manhunt for
Eddie Morales, who police believe ambushed popular Holyoke cop John
DiNapoli, spreads to Connecticut and New Hampshire. Latino
community worries that the aggressive search will compound already
poor relations with the police. By Jordana Hart. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   DEAD-MOTHER (Peabody, Mass.) _ School board announces its
support for teacher Janet Makar, who took no action after
first-grader Lydia Hanson said her mother was dead. By Marcella
Bombardieri. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   FBI-INDICTMENT (Boston) _ Although federal prosecutors say the
investigation into wrongdoing by FBI agents is still alive in the
wake of the indictment of retired star agent John Connolly, any
probe will be hampered by the five-year statute of limitations. By
Shelley Murphy. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   CONCAVE-CHEST (Boston) _ Doctor at Massachusetts General uses a
tool similar to an automotive dent puller to treat a condition
known as sunken chest. Procedure is minimally invasive, doc says.
By Richard Saltus. 850 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   NASDAQ-RECORD (Undated) _ It's a Merry Christmas on Wall Street
as the Nasdaq composite index tops 4000 less than two months after
passing 3000. Venerable Dow Jones also on track to hit its first
record close since August. By Ronald Rosenberg. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BKN-CELTICS-FORTSON (Boston) _ Celtics activate Danny Fortson
from the injured list. To make room on the roster, Jamel Thomas is
placed on waivers. By Shira Springer. 800 words.
</P>
