 &QL; 
BEANIE _ Ty Inc., based in suburban Chicago, is expected to
announce its next product line Christmas Eve day. The company has
already announced that Beanie Babies will be discontinued as of
Dec. 31, and fans of this phenomenon are wondering what will happen
A) next and B) to the value of their collections. The story
outlines the background, has quotes from Phoenix area Beanie Baby
traders and contains industry overview. By DAVE WALKER. Story will
move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
ASTHMA (Scottsdale, Ariz.) - The Mayo Clinic in Scottsdale is
trying to find a gene associated with asthma, which is on the rise
among minority and low-income populations. Story focuses on the
clinic's research, which is funded by the American Lung
Association, and tells the story through a family of asthma
sufferers. By KERRY FEHR-SNYDER. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
NINETEEN (Undated) - I am the number 19, and my days are numbered.
</P>
<P>
   You've heard the news, you've seen the future, you've checked
your calendar. The countdown is on, and yours truly, Nineteen, is
being eighty-sixed. I, 19, look back sadly, and regret that I may
have taken this fleeting life for granted. I should have savored
every moment. But now that I think of it, I guess hindsight is 20 _
aw, forget it. By MARK JONATHAN DAVIS, Special for The Arizona
Republi9c. &QL;
</P>
