   RUSSIA-TALBOTT (Moscow) _ Deputy Secretary of State Strobe
Talbott ends two days of talks on a sour note, accusing Russia of
``indiscriminate killing'' in Chechnya and without breaking a
lingering stalemate between Washington and Moscow over a major arms
control treaty. As Russian forces continue to pound rebel positions
in the breakaway republic of Chechnya, Talbott offered some of the
harshest American criticism to date of the Kremlin's military
campaign. By Celestine Bohlen. (The story has moved in ``i'' news
file.) 1,100 words.
