<P>
   NY-CREW-MAYOR (New York) _ As recently as last week, Mayor
Rudolph Giuliani was grudgingly content to leave the fate of his
former friend, Schools Chancellor Rudy Crew, in the hands of the
seven members of the Board of Education. After all, the mayor is on
the verge of declaring his candidacy for the Senate and needs
stability. But in recent days, people close to the issue say,
Giuliani became fed up with the long-playing Rudy Crew psychodrama
and let it be known that the chancellor's ouster would make a fine
Christmas present. By Dan Barry. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in
``a'' news file.) 1,300 words.
