   SAFRICA-SUBURBS (Mayville, South Africa) _ The modest one-room
houses in this fledgling black suburb are the most tangible symbol
of the post-apartheid government's commitment to redressing South
Africa's stark inequalities. And the changing lives within the
brick walls offer an intimate view of the hopes and hardships of
ordinary black people still struggling to climb the economic and
