allegedly misdiagnosed the patient's problem as hemorrhoids. &UR;  &LR; Also,
after affording Whalen the chance to present evidence by Jan. 12,
the Massachusetts Board of Registration will then decide whether to
reaffirm its Dec. 22 summary suspension. Whalen then has the right
to a hearing within seven days.
