   BC-GIULIANI-TIETELBAUM-NYT (moved on Tuesday, Dec. 21.)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, Dec. 21,
about Bruce Teitelbaum, an adviser to Mayor Rudolph W. Giuliani who
has been under scrutiny for his role in dealing with Hasidic
builders in Brooklyn, misstated an account from Brooklyn
prosecutors about their interviewing of Anthony V. Carbonetti,
Giuliani's chief of staff. According to prosecutors, Carbonetti
spoke with investigators once in person and later by telephone. But
they say the telephone conversation was initiated by the Brooklyn
District Attorney's office, not by Carbonetti.
</P>
